,Recommended,528660,29125733,Posted: 8 January,all,Athravan,"Confession time - I received a 90% off coupon when crafting an unrelated badge; so I picked the game up for a grand total of 8 pennies. Why did I buy a game I had zero interest in realistically? Look, I'm an addict, and it has cards that sell for more - so I can make some mad crazy profits too (*cough* 15p profit... not quite enough for a Freddo anymore)!Guilt ridden for purchasing so many games that I don't play, I made an attempt at sticking to a New Years Resolution of ""Don't buy the bloody thing if you won't play it"", and I faffed around for an hour, spinning boxes and generally coming to the realization that I have bad co-ordination and am easily distracted.This game is the very essence of distraction. Bright colours, drifting shapes, flashing backgrounds and zingy music that is hyperactive at best and downright deranged at some points. It's not meant to be soothing, that much is obvious - it's meant to do everything it can to distract you from the task, and that's how it aims to pose a challenge.Coloured balls drop from the ceiling. Sometimes they say a different colour to what they are - madness! Sometimes they hit a coloured line and they change colour half way down, which plays a double mind-trick on your eyes and brain. You have to flip the box (well it starts as a simple box and progresses to a harder hexagon) and match the colours. One mistake, game over. There are a couple of game modes that affect shapes and speed that you can unlock.It's a very very simple game designed to tax your brain and eyes for an hour or two at most. It has little longevity past that point, but it should appeal to people wanting something to focus on for an hour, something to play in a study break that won't be too addictive, or for those who like achievements, as you could probably 100% the game fairly quickly if you're not a half-blind geriatric like me.Pros:Very cheap, with trading cards.Successfully challenges brain and eyes to make colour / word connections.Effective use of shapes, colours and music as distraction.Bite-size game for when you just want to distract yourself for a short period.Possible to 100% in an hour if you're an achievement lover.Cons:Short, perhaps too easy for those who are looking for a serious challenge.Play for more than an hour at a time and you'll probably get a headache.Could easily be improved with the addition of daily / all time leaderboards to add a reason to keep playing,In short, not bad - smooth controls and easy to pick up. Very cheap game to begin with, but available in sales and with coupons for much cheaper, so grab it if you're bored."
