,Recommended,528660,29503330,Posted: 26 January,all,[Hex] RottenB,"Okay, first things first, I think I got this game for around 9 Cent or so, as I used a Coupon.Secondly, this is a game that totally fits my style as I'm a dude that got every single achievement in ""Super Hexagon"", a game with a similar premise.The game in itself is totally okay for a 0.99€ game. You have a Square/Hexagon and flying orbs with a color of one side of your shape. The orbs must fly into the right color so you win a point and another orb spawns. Through time you unlock new gamemodes which are as followed:Fast ModeHexagon ModeWord ModeTime ModeTrip ModeFlip Modenot yet releasedThese levels all give lots of content that can hook you for an hour or two. Totally fine there.While I think the Gameplay is fluid and is mostly fair I do have some minor problems with the normal mode.The normal mode is (as described in the game) a mode where all other modes are combined. That's totally ok and whilst I haven't seen the Trip mode up to this point I'm kinda ok with that.The problem there lies in the switching times between modes. As an example when entering Hexagon Mode the Square has a short morphing time in which the next orb/ dot already comes flying at you but you cannot change the direction your (then Hexagon) is facing, therefore giving you more or less half the time you had beforehand for more spins.Another problem there is, that the color that faced beforehand the top/bottom changes when morphing in and out of Hexagon-mode making it impossible to predict how often you'll need to spin afterwards.But other than that I have only experienced one time while Hexagon-Mode switched off and Flip mode started in the same time that 3 orbs came at the same time with different colors... Not sure what went off there but with multiple tries I could not reconstruct that scenario after that one time...The only other thing that I think could take some improvement are the different unlockable modes. While I did enjoy most of them (except Trip Mode, bc that's literally the worst thing or I'm just too stupid) I think that it would've been more enjoyable to input them so, that the player could choose which one of them he wants to play and also play MULTIPLE AT THE SAME TIME.Personally I think that a Time+Hexagon-Mode would be perfect and up to this point it doesn't seem that there's a way to play a mode like that.So tl;dr:While the game isn't perfect it's totally worth 0,99€. If the developer implements a way to play multiple modes at the same time (while not putting all of them at random like in normal mode) I'd say I would like the game even more. But as it stands I can still recommend this game to people who crave some lil fun."
