76561198048921689,Recommended,528660,33008598,Posted: 29 June,all,Spooky,"I have mixed feelings about this one. I was expecting something challenging, enjoyable, just like the trailer shows. First few minutes were pretty much that, but after that you'll see the little things which you can't just ""unsee"". Most importantly the off-centered cube/hexagon annoyed me a lot, and I don't even have OCD.I'm not nitpicking, but some parts of UI weren't as much straightforward as they could be, also the UI gets messed up in lower resolution (or maybe it was because of 2K display?). During the gameplay there is quite a lot of effects, but I didn't understand the ""shattered glass"" floating up, it just didn't blend in to the overall design. Just the fading and changing colors would do the job, too.I was happy for reasonble amount of achievements until I found out how extremely easy I can get them. Even a person who never played such genre of games could consider them as easy to get. Of course not counting the last one, reach level 30 - I was really not enjoying playing the game as much at that stage. I spent 77 minutes playing this game, half of the time getting that last achievement.Please don't get me wrong, I was really hyped for this game as I love rage games, but it hasn't fulfilled my expectations. It feels like it used only half of its potential, otherwise it could be a very good game.My rating: 5/10, but for its price it is a fair deal.And by the way, who put that giant restart button to the center of the screen in pause?!"
,Not Recommended,528660,33628442,Posted: 18 July,all,MrDowntempo,"This game has a creative puzzle mechanic and flashy colorful graphics. It shuold be a solid puzzler. Unfortunetly, it has some major problems in the balance department. Certain modes are absurdly easy. You could essentially play the words mode indefinetly without losing. And then on the other end of the spectrum, there are some situations that are simply unwinable. In the normal mode, which combines the mechanics from all te other modes, this is a huge problem because it otherwise is the most interesting game mode. When the box switches to a hexagon or switches back there is a little animation, but that animation eats up time and can, in certain situations, make it impossible for you to rotate to the right color in time. Also there is one mode where you must keep turning the box, but in normal mode, there's no cue to let the player know they need to meet this requirement. This can cause frustrating defeats that don't seem fair. On top of this, there are some other minor issues, such as no volume/music sliders, just the ability to turn ALL sound on or off. Really a shame, because with a little more attention, this could be a fantastic gem of a twitch puzzle game."
